  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Six stabbed to death in Devinuwara",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Matara High Court Judge Tamara Tennakoon has sentenced to death six people, including Chamil, a well - known drug dealer in the South, who was convicted of killing five people in a van carrying a group of people 22 years ago.",
        "The death sentences were handed down by Devinuwara Narathota Hewage Thamil Ajith Kumara alias Kudu Chamil, Sumith Kumara, Saunda Hennadige Chaminda, Abeyratne Magampattu Maha Vidanage Namal, Abeyratne Weerasekera Patabendige Roshan Dilruksha, Abeyterana Weerasekera Pathabendige Nishaki.",
        "On or about November 14, 2000, they shot and killed five people in front of a clock tower in front of the Devinuwara Clock Tower."
      ],
